WEBVTT

00:00.474 --> 00:02.474
I came to see what you think

00:02.476 --> 00:04.109
about me coming with you
to Chicago.

00:04.111 --> 00:06.044
There's a school
in upstate New York.

00:06.046 --> 00:08.179
Ten years ago Discharge Power
started making batteries,

00:08.180 --> 00:10.081
and those kids started
getting lead poisoning.

00:10.083 --> 00:12.517
And they say it's not
from the plant, but it is.

00:12.519 --> 00:14.352
This is a list of children
pulled from the school

00:14.354 --> 00:16.454
within the first six months
of the plant opening.

00:16.456 --> 00:18.156
The parents are all executives
at Discharge Power.

00:18.158 --> 00:19.758
100,000 a family.

00:19.760 --> 00:21.559
It's a lawsuit on behalf
of your former partners

00:21.561 --> 00:24.362
for damages incurred by the
criminal actions of this firm.

00:24.364 --> 00:25.597
Give these guys
their jobs back,

00:25.599 --> 00:27.198
this whole thing goes away.

00:27.200 --> 00:29.234
I got a job offer today.
It's in Seattle.

00:29.236 --> 00:30.602
What if I told you
I'd consider it?

00:30.604 --> 00:32.470
You told me they were
gonna offer me a job.

00:32.472 --> 00:34.139
You gave me a reason
to take it,

00:34.141 --> 00:35.440
and then when I didn't
jump on it,

00:35.442 --> 00:37.275
you put people that I care
about out of work.

00:37.277 --> 00:39.244
Holy shit, Gordon
doesn't want to take over.

00:39.246 --> 00:41.346
He just wants to orchestrate a
deal where his guys come back,

00:41.348 --> 00:44.382
they vote to merge with Zane,
and we cease to exist.

00:44.384 --> 00:46.117
<i>I just found out</i>
<i>that my two partners</i>

00:46.119 --> 00:48.119
are willing to stab me
in the back.

00:48.121 --> 00:50.355
I'm sorry I had to be the one
to break it to you, Robert,

00:50.357 --> 00:52.424
but you better get
your house in order,

00:52.426 --> 00:55.160
because now I have
to protect mine.

00:55.162 --> 00:57.328
I went out there
to make a difference,

00:57.330 --> 00:59.831
so I decided
to go toe-to-toe

00:59.833 --> 01:03.068
with the mayor's office
on a police brutality case.

01:03.070 --> 01:04.836
Two weeks after
you put out that statement,

01:04.837 --> 01:06.471
they came after my license.

01:06.473 --> 01:08.506
What exactly do you want
me to do about it?

01:08.508 --> 01:11.810
I want you to stand next to me
on the last case I'll ever have.

01:11.812 --> 01:13.611
You can have your pick
of the top guys out there.

01:13.613 --> 01:16.114
I don't need the top guy.

01:16.116 --> 01:18.650
I need the best partner
I've ever had.

01:22.155 --> 01:24.289
[horn honking]
- Robert.

01:24.291 --> 01:26.224
Oh, you have got to be
shitting me.

01:26.226 --> 01:27.559
This is the worst possible time
for you to be around here.

01:27.561 --> 01:30.228
I don't care.
I need your help with Gordon.

01:30.230 --> 01:31.663
What the hell
do you need help for?

01:31.665 --> 01:33.298
All you have to do to get
out of this mess

01:33.300 --> 01:34.632
is not bring those
partners back

01:34.634 --> 01:36.468
and just fight this thing
on its merits.

01:36.470 --> 01:38.436
Yeah, if we fight this thing
on its own merits and lose,

01:38.438 --> 01:41.206
we won't have a firm anymore.
- Well, that's not my problem.

01:41.208 --> 01:43.575
And even if it was, what am I
supposed to do about it?

01:43.577 --> 01:45.543
You tell those partners
that you're not gonna waive

01:45.545 --> 01:47.178
their non-competes,
and if they don't drop the case

01:47.180 --> 01:48.346
you'll fire them.
- And if I did that,

01:48.348 --> 01:50.315
they'd fire me.
- Bullshit.

01:50.317 --> 01:52.550
You have bylaws to protect you.
- No, listen to me, God damn it.

01:52.552 --> 01:54.853
I'm gonna tell you
the same thing I told Harvey.

01:54.855 --> 01:56.588
I'm in this shitstorm

01:56.590 --> 01:58.623
because of my chummy
relationship with your firm.

01:58.625 --> 02:01.159
I do that,
bylaws or no,

02:01.161 --> 02:02.861
I'm out on my ass.
- Robert, please.

02:02.863 --> 02:05.330
We are talking
about your daughter's home.

02:05.332 --> 02:08.500
Don't you dare use my daughter
as a bargaining chip.

02:08.502 --> 02:11.569
She's a grown-ass woman.
She can take care of herself.

02:11.571 --> 02:15.573
So, like Harvey said,
you take care of your house

02:15.575 --> 02:17.609
because I'm gonna take care
of mine.

02:17.611 --> 02:20.145
<i>[bluesy music]</i>

02:20.147 --> 02:27.252
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:29.000 --> 02:35.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:36.930 --> 02:38.630
[grunts]
What the hell?

02:38.632 --> 02:40.431
Hey, buddy,
you just walked into me.

02:40.433 --> 02:42.267
Are you kidding me?
You just walked through me

02:42.269 --> 02:43.635
at 60 miles an hour.

02:43.637 --> 02:45.336
Well, then I would
keep my head up if I were you.

02:45.338 --> 02:47.505
You're not in Kansas anymore.

02:47.507 --> 02:50.208
- What'd you say to me?
- I said this is Chicago.

02:50.210 --> 02:51.543
And you're not
in Kansas anymore.

02:51.545 --> 02:52.644
Well, it might as well
be Kansas to me,

02:52.646 --> 02:54.179
because I'm from New York.

02:54.181 --> 02:55.547
Now get the hell
out of my face.

02:55.549 --> 02:58.216
Oh, I know where you're from,
Mr. Specter.

02:58.218 --> 02:59.651
And if you think you're gonna
stop Pat McGann

02:59.653 --> 03:01.719
from doing what he does,
you might as well turn around,

03:01.721 --> 03:03.388
check your little man purse,

03:03.390 --> 03:05.290
and go back to wherever
the hell you came from.

03:05.292 --> 03:08.293
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

03:08.295 --> 03:15.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:16.403 --> 03:18.269
Where are you going,
young lady?

03:18.271 --> 03:20.338
- To school.
- Not like that, you're not.

03:20.340 --> 03:22.774
Your uniform's supposed
to be buttoned up all the way.

03:22.776 --> 03:24.542
I told you kids
make fun of me.

03:24.544 --> 03:28.413
And I told you that's
exactly why you do it.

03:28.415 --> 03:29.781
You're at war,

03:29.783 --> 03:32.283
and you don't let the world
see your weak spots.

03:32.285 --> 03:33.985
And who exactly
am I at war with?

03:33.987 --> 03:36.287
With the world.
'Cause if it was up to them,

03:36.289 --> 03:39.357
you'd be living in poverty
your entire life like...

03:40.961 --> 03:42.527
Like who, Dad?

03:42.529 --> 03:44.562
And what does it have to do
with how I dress?

03:44.564 --> 03:46.297
It has everything
to do with it.

03:46.299 --> 03:48.366
Because if they see
one imperfection,

03:48.368 --> 03:50.702
they're going to pull
on that string.

03:50.704 --> 03:53.504
And the next thing you know,
you're going to be laid bare.

03:53.506 --> 03:56.608
Dad, I'm just a girl.

03:56.610 --> 03:59.978
And if you think like that,
Jessica Pearson,

03:59.980 --> 04:02.447
that's all you'll ever be.

04:02.449 --> 04:05.450
<i>[dramatic piano music]</i>

04:05.452 --> 04:12.557
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:15.662 --> 04:17.795
You getting ready for
the hearing this morning?

04:17.797 --> 04:19.797
You know I am.

04:19.798 --> 04:21.699
Let me handle this for you,
Jessica.

04:21.701 --> 04:23.601
I told you,
I want Harvey on this.

04:23.603 --> 04:25.003
You did tell me that,

04:25.005 --> 04:27.038
but I'm still a little hazy
as to why.

04:27.040 --> 04:29.407
For one thing,
you're a partner in a law firm.

04:29.409 --> 04:32.677
- And so is Harvey.
- In New York, not Chicago.

04:32.679 --> 04:36.281
Which means anything I ask him
to do won't backfire onto you.

04:36.283 --> 04:38.283
Jessica,
I'm not worried about me.

04:38.285 --> 04:40.618
Jeff, we've talked
about this.

04:40.620 --> 04:42.387
I can handle myself.

04:42.389 --> 04:44.055
And I'm sure
that's exactly what

04:44.057 --> 04:46.758
the original plaintiff thought
right before he turned up dead.

04:46.760 --> 04:48.626
Come on.

04:48.628 --> 04:50.395
Do you know how many people
have been shot

04:50.397 --> 04:53.298
in that neighborhood
over the past ten years?

04:53.300 --> 04:55.366
One has nothing
to do with the other.

04:55.368 --> 04:59.470
All I'm saying is that
you've been through something.

04:59.472 --> 05:01.506
And apart from
the loss of a child,

05:01.508 --> 05:05.376
it's--it's the biggest thing
that you could ever go through.

05:05.378 --> 05:09.781
And I love that you're
looking out for me.

05:09.783 --> 05:13.518
But that thing is exactly why
I'm taking on this fight.

05:13.520 --> 05:16.354
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:16.356 --> 05:19.090
I know.

05:19.092 --> 05:21.592
And I just wanna make sure that
when you march into battle,

05:21.594 --> 05:24.495
you've got your eyes open.

05:24.497 --> 05:29.467
Jeff, I'm taking on
the city of Chicago.

05:29.469 --> 05:30.735
Believe me,

05:30.737 --> 05:32.674
my eyes are wide
goddamn open.

05:32.675 --> 05:36.675
<b><font color="#00FF00">♪ Suits 7x16 ♪</font></b>
