06:05.337 --> 06:07.204
<i>♪ The greenback boogie ♪</i>

06:08.743 --> 06:12.845
Ladies and gentlemen,
I appreciate you coming today.

06:12.847 --> 06:16.582
I know your time is valuable,
so I'll just cut to the chase.

06:16.584 --> 06:18.684
School.

06:18.686 --> 06:21.687
It's where our kids
are taught and nurtured.

06:21.689 --> 06:23.823
And it's supposed to be
their safest place.

06:23.825 --> 06:26.826
But for the families
of Treetop Elementary,

06:26.828 --> 06:29.662
Discharge Power
took that safety away

06:29.664 --> 06:30.963
when they built
a battery plant

06:30.965 --> 06:34.267
1,000 yards away
from their playground.

06:34.269 --> 06:36.836
Now, they're gonna say they
took the proper precautions.

06:36.838 --> 06:38.638
They didn't.

06:38.640 --> 06:40.973
And now hundreds of innocent
children are suffering

06:40.975 --> 06:43.543
the devastating effects
of lead poisoning,

06:43.545 --> 06:45.011
and they will never
be the same.

06:45.013 --> 06:47.647
One of the first things
we all learned in school

06:47.649 --> 06:49.949
was to treat others as we
would be treated ourselves.

06:49.951 --> 06:51.951
But, ladies and gentlemen
of the jury,

06:51.953 --> 06:56.756
you and I together are going
to teach Discharge Power

06:56.758 --> 06:57.924
the lesson
they should have learned

06:57.926 --> 07:00.092
when they were five years old.

07:00.094 --> 07:02.728
- How'd it go with Zane?
- I'll tell you how it went.

07:02.730 --> 07:05.331
I got a big fat bowl of,
"You're on your own."

07:05.333 --> 07:06.832
You told him how serious
this was?

07:06.834 --> 07:08.568
Yes, and he already knew.

07:08.570 --> 07:09.769
What about appealing
to the father in him?

07:09.771 --> 07:11.003
I'm not an idiot, Donna.
I tried that.

07:11.005 --> 07:12.738
And the second I did,
he bit my head off.

07:12.740 --> 07:14.073
Okay, well, we have to think
of something.

07:14.075 --> 07:15.775
I know that, and right now,
the only thing

07:15.777 --> 07:17.610
I can think of is letting
the partners come back,

07:17.612 --> 07:19.645
because I cannot find
a way to prove

07:19.647 --> 07:21.647
that they weren't harmed
by what we did.

07:21.649 --> 07:23.015
I might have a way.

07:23.017 --> 07:24.283
No time for guessing games,
Alex.

07:24.285 --> 07:26.018
What do you got?
- Think about it.

07:26.020 --> 07:27.687
What is Gordon offering
these guys if they come back?

07:27.689 --> 07:29.322
They vote us out and they
merge with Zane,

07:29.324 --> 07:31.057
which means he offering them
better jobs and more money.

07:31.059 --> 07:32.925
And what if we got them
all that somewhere else?

07:32.927 --> 07:35.094
We'd not only get rid of them;
we'd proved they weren't harmed

07:35.096 --> 07:36.829
by you, Harvey,
or anyone else.

07:36.831 --> 07:38.598
Well, that's a great idea,
Alex, but where the hell

07:38.600 --> 07:40.933
are we gonna find someone
to give 25 partners

07:40.935 --> 07:43.836
raises and promotions
at some other major law firm?

07:43.838 --> 07:45.705
I'll tell them where
we're gonna find them, Louis.

07:45.707 --> 07:46.973
Where I left them.

07:46.975 --> 07:49.742
Right inside your
motherfucking Dictaphone.

07:49.744 --> 07:52.745
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:52.747 --> 07:55.348
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:55.350 --> 07:57.617
- You look determined.
- I am.

07:57.619 --> 07:59.752
You double-check that power
of attorney I sent you?

07:59.754 --> 08:01.053
- I did.
- And how about

08:01.055 --> 08:02.788
your application
to practice in Illinois?

08:02.790 --> 08:04.056
It needs to be airtight.

08:04.058 --> 08:05.858
I'm good to practice here
for a month.

08:05.860 --> 08:08.928
I had Donna file it herself.
- Good.

08:08.930 --> 08:11.364
Jessica...

08:11.366 --> 08:13.099
what have we gotten ourselves
into here?

08:13.101 --> 08:14.867
What do you mean?

08:14.869 --> 08:16.936
I mean someone was waiting
for me at the airport,

08:16.938 --> 08:20.139
and it wasn't a town car.

08:20.141 --> 08:22.942
Harvey, I told you.

08:22.944 --> 08:24.810
These people here
are no joke.

08:24.812 --> 08:26.679
They're trying
to run me out of town.

08:26.681 --> 08:28.814
Well, they're not too happy
about me being here, either.

08:28.816 --> 08:31.017
Then let's get in there
and get this damn thing done.

08:31.019 --> 08:35.988
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:35.990 --> 08:37.756
Hey, I was looking
for you earlier.

08:37.759 --> 08:39.357
How'd it go?

08:39.360 --> 08:41.059
Far as the opening statements
went, it was good.

08:41.062 --> 08:42.895
But then
the judge got pulled away,

08:42.897 --> 08:45.197
which means we lost momentum,
and then on top of that,

08:45.199 --> 08:46.999
I just found out
that the soil samples

08:47.001 --> 08:50.836
that we were supposed
to have last night got delayed.

08:50.838 --> 08:52.705
You don't think
Discharge Power

08:52.707 --> 08:53.873
had anything to do with it,
do you?

08:53.875 --> 08:55.708
I didn't until
you just said that.

08:55.710 --> 08:58.411
I'm just saying,
look at what they already did.

08:58.413 --> 09:00.846
They offered you a fake job,
and then the same guy

09:00.848 --> 09:02.948
had your donor shut down
the whole clinic.

09:02.950 --> 09:04.383
I mean, Mike, if they're
willing to do that--

09:04.385 --> 09:06.118
Shit.

09:06.120 --> 09:07.920
If we don't get those samples,
we are in trouble.

09:07.922 --> 09:09.155
Maybe we don't need them.

09:09.157 --> 09:10.723
If we can prove
they did all that,

09:10.725 --> 09:12.091
it's obstruction.

09:12.093 --> 09:13.693
We prove that,
we don't need any soil samples.

09:13.695 --> 09:14.994
What can I do?

09:14.996 --> 09:16.162
You work on finding out
the connection

09:16.164 --> 09:17.997
between Andy Forsyth
and the donors.

09:17.999 --> 09:20.099
I'm gonna figure out what to do
if those samples do show up.

09:20.101 --> 09:25.137
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:25.139 --> 09:26.806
Your Honor, Harvey Specter.

09:26.808 --> 09:27.940
I'm representing the residents

09:27.942 --> 09:29.208
of the North Park
Housing Project.

09:29.210 --> 09:31.444
Great.
All we need is Ms. Allen,

09:31.446 --> 09:33.145
and we can actually
accomplish something.

09:33.147 --> 09:35.014
Sorry I'm late, Your Honor.

09:35.016 --> 09:37.016
I had to put my contacts in
to make sure I was actually

09:37.018 --> 09:39.051
seeing Jessica Pearson
in your chambers.

09:39.053 --> 09:40.853
- And why wouldn't I be here?
- Because this is

09:40.855 --> 09:42.788
a lawyers-only meeting,
and you're not licensed

09:42.790 --> 09:44.156
to practice law in this state.
- And the last time I checked,

09:44.158 --> 09:45.925
I don't need a license
to be the plaintiff.

09:45.927 --> 09:47.993
No, but you do need to live
in public housing,

09:47.995 --> 09:51.030
which generally requires
not wearing $3,000 shoes.

09:51.032 --> 09:52.998
Power of attorney signed
by Lillian Cook

09:53.000 --> 09:54.166
to Jessica Pearson, Your Honor.

09:54.168 --> 09:55.901
She's a plaintiff
under the law.

09:55.903 --> 09:57.470
Your Honor, I don't care
what that thing says.

09:57.472 --> 09:59.171
This project's been in
the works for three years,

09:59.173 --> 10:00.506
and they are just stepping in
at the last minute

10:00.508 --> 10:02.208
to get publicity.

10:02.210 --> 10:04.744
We're stepping in because the
wrecking ball is about to fly,

10:04.746 --> 10:06.779
and you are not living up
to your end of the bargain.

10:06.781 --> 10:08.180
If you're referring
to the percentage

10:08.182 --> 10:09.815
of low-income housing,

10:09.817 --> 10:11.083
some minor adjustments
were made.

10:11.085 --> 10:13.819
Minor? You stood
in front of city council

10:13.821 --> 10:16.288
and gave your word
that 35% of this development

10:16.290 --> 10:18.924
would be reserved
for public housing.

10:18.926 --> 10:22.261
The latest plans show
only 5% are going there,

10:22.263 --> 10:24.830
and to hell with everyone else.
- Where did you get that?

10:24.832 --> 10:26.499
That is not part
of the public record.

10:26.501 --> 10:28.234
Well, neither is the fact
that a shady developer

10:28.236 --> 10:31.003
is ripping off the poor
to line his own pockets,

10:31.005 --> 10:33.139
and you're helping him.
- Don't you say that to me.

10:33.141 --> 10:34.840
I don't represent Pat McGann.

10:34.842 --> 10:37.243
I represent the city
I've lived in my whole life.

10:37.245 --> 10:40.112
And all you care about
is making a name for yourself

10:40.114 --> 10:43.115
by using some poor woman.
- I'm not using anyone.

10:43.117 --> 10:45.117
And you can--
- Okay, that's enough.

10:45.119 --> 10:47.086
Ms. Pearson,
if I deem you to be

10:47.088 --> 10:49.922
manipulating this Lillian Cook
for your own purposes,

10:49.924 --> 10:51.557
I will shut
this thing down myself.

10:51.559 --> 10:52.825
Your Honor,
how can my client prove to you

10:52.827 --> 10:54.059
what's in her heart?

10:54.061 --> 10:55.194
I don't care
what's in her heart.

10:55.196 --> 10:56.796
I want to hear from this woman,

10:56.798 --> 10:58.297
and I want to hear from her
tomorrow.

10:58.299 --> 11:03.269
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:03.271 --> 11:06.505
Eli, I'm glad I caught you.
You got a minute?

11:06.507 --> 11:08.908
Actually, Alex,
I've got a lunch, so--

11:08.910 --> 11:10.843
That wasn't a question.
It was a statement.

11:10.845 --> 11:12.978
Let me guess.
This is about that lawsuit

11:12.980 --> 11:16.081
Stanley Gordon filed
on behalf of your ex-partners.

11:16.083 --> 11:17.850
Well, you can just turn
yourself right around,

11:17.852 --> 11:19.585
because my heart isn't exactly
bleeding for you.

11:19.587 --> 11:21.353
I don't give a shit
what your heart is doing, Eli.

11:21.355 --> 11:23.589
'Cause I'm not here
for your sympathy.

11:23.591 --> 11:25.925
I'm here 'cause you're gonna
give every one of those

11:25.927 --> 11:27.359
bastards a job.
- You son of a bitch.

11:27.361 --> 11:28.961
Don't give me that.

11:28.963 --> 11:29.995
Your partner set me up
for murder,

11:29.997 --> 11:31.564
and you didn't bat an eye.

11:31.566 --> 11:34.233
So I make offers to more
than 15 of those guys.

11:34.235 --> 11:37.336
They won't take those jobs
anyway because we don't have

11:37.338 --> 11:39.271
that kind of money,
and everybody knows it.

11:39.273 --> 11:42.007
So it's either 15
or put me away.

11:42.009 --> 11:45.144
'Cause that's the best
you're gonna get.

11:45.146 --> 11:46.879
15.

11:46.881 --> 11:49.281
Raises and promotions
for every goddamn one of them.

11:49.283 --> 11:55.287
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:55.289 --> 11:57.990
You know, the architecture
here is stunning.

11:57.992 --> 12:00.259
If I worked here,
I'd be in a much better mood

12:00.261 --> 12:01.994
than you seem to be.

12:01.996 --> 12:03.295
I have nothing to say to you
outside of court.

12:03.297 --> 12:06.198
I'm trying to avoid
court altogether.

12:06.200 --> 12:07.633
What do you want,
Ms. Pearson?

12:07.635 --> 12:09.168
I want a sit-down
with the mayor.

12:09.170 --> 12:11.203
[laughs]
Well, that's not gonna happen.

12:11.205 --> 12:13.038
You're his right hand.
You can walk right into

12:13.040 --> 12:15.040
his office and make it happen.
- I'm not his right hand.

12:15.042 --> 12:17.009
I'm the City Attorney,
and I don't have time

12:17.011 --> 12:18.944
to arrange courtesy meetings
for people who go after

12:18.946 --> 12:20.579
our civil servants.
- Look, I know there's

12:20.581 --> 12:23.215
bad blood with
the 13th precinct situation.

12:23.217 --> 12:25.985
I'm just looking for
some sort of accommodation.

12:25.987 --> 12:29.188
And what makes you think
I have the power to do that?

12:29.190 --> 12:31.123
All I do is represent
the city's interest

12:31.125 --> 12:33.058
without passion or prejudice.

12:33.060 --> 12:37.229
And which one was it without
when you came for my license?

12:37.231 --> 12:39.198
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

12:39.200 --> 12:41.066
And what about the mayor?
Does he know?

12:41.068 --> 12:43.168
Or is that why you don't want
me talking to him?

12:43.170 --> 12:45.938
Because if I did,
I'd tell him he's up

12:45.940 --> 12:47.606
for reelection in six months,

12:47.608 --> 12:49.909
and this project
doesn't look good for him.

12:49.911 --> 12:52.611
Whatever it is
you think you know--

12:52.613 --> 12:55.347
if there's any understanding
to be had on this project,

12:55.349 --> 12:58.150
you're gonna have to come
to it with Pat McGann.

12:58.152 --> 13:00.920
Not me, and not the mayor.

13:00.922 --> 13:02.421
And let me give you
a free piece of advice.

13:02.423 --> 13:05.224
This is Chicago.
If you wanna get something done,

13:05.226 --> 13:07.026
you're gonna need more than
your Louboutins

13:07.028 --> 13:09.061
and your holier-than-thou
attitude.

13:15.038 --> 13:17.238
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

13:17.240 --> 13:18.572
11, okay?

13:18.574 --> 13:20.207
And don't let them skimp
on any of the materials--

13:20.209 --> 13:21.375
Patrick McGann?

13:23.246 --> 13:25.212
Give us a minute, will you?

13:25.214 --> 13:28.182
You must be Jessica Pearson.
- You know who I am.

13:28.184 --> 13:30.117
Well, I've never
seen your picture,

13:30.119 --> 13:33.254
but there aren't a lot of women
that match your description.

13:33.256 --> 13:35.456
Now, what can I do for you,
Jessica?

13:35.458 --> 13:37.558
You can hire me
to find another location

13:37.560 --> 13:39.260
for your project
that doesn't throw people

13:39.262 --> 13:41.062
out of their homes.

13:41.064 --> 13:44.065
As much as I'd like to spend
time getting to know you,

13:44.067 --> 13:45.533
there's no way you and I
working together

13:45.535 --> 13:48.202
is in our future.

13:48.204 --> 13:51.138
And what if I told you you'd
regret making that decision?

13:51.140 --> 13:54.275
Well, I'd say that you can
stop trying to get to the mayor

13:54.277 --> 13:56.277
because he's not taking
a meeting with you.

13:56.279 --> 13:59.180
And you can take that
to the bank.

13:59.182 --> 14:02.149
Because I'm the one
that makes the decisions here.

14:02.151 --> 14:04.552
Is that really something you
want to be saying to me?

14:04.554 --> 14:06.554
You think he doesn't know
how it works?

14:06.556 --> 14:10.558
I think it's not legal
to trade money for influence.

14:10.560 --> 14:14.295
And you should be careful
who you say that to.

14:14.297 --> 14:17.398
Every nickel
I've ever given Bobby Novak

14:17.400 --> 14:19.433
is aboveboard.

14:19.435 --> 14:21.235
So why don't you just
go put that woman

14:21.237 --> 14:23.170
on the stand tomorrow
and be done with it?

14:23.172 --> 14:26.374
Because I guarantee you,
when this is over,

14:26.376 --> 14:28.142
my building's going up.

14:28.144 --> 14:35.249
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:39.389 --> 14:41.389
[distant baby crying]

14:44.327 --> 14:45.659
[knocking]

14:47.230 --> 14:48.596
Lillian Cook?

14:52.335 --> 14:53.334
Could be.
Who are you?

14:53.336 --> 14:54.602
My name is Harvey Specter.

14:54.604 --> 14:56.604
I'm here to prepare you
for court.

14:56.606 --> 14:58.339
What do you mean, court?

14:58.341 --> 15:00.241
I mean if you want
to stay in your home,

15:00.243 --> 15:01.709
you're gonna have to testify.
And it's gonna be tomorrow.

15:01.711 --> 15:03.277
No.
Uh-uh.

15:03.279 --> 15:04.512
Jessica Pearson's
handling that.

15:04.514 --> 15:06.280
She sent me here to help.

15:07.583 --> 15:10.351
Well, you tell her
I don't need help from someone

15:10.353 --> 15:12.353
who doesn't know me
and, from the looks of him,

15:12.355 --> 15:14.622
thinks this whole place
is a piece of garbage.

15:14.624 --> 15:18.092
What I think is you lived
here most of your life,

15:18.094 --> 15:19.693
and now you're gonna get kicked
into the street

15:19.695 --> 15:23.164
because they didn't live up
to their end of the bargain.

15:25.568 --> 15:29.136
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:29.138 --> 15:30.571
You a coffee man,
or are you one of them

15:30.573 --> 15:33.240
chai latte drinking
pretty boys?

15:33.242 --> 15:34.408
Both.

15:34.410 --> 15:36.310
I'm a coffee man
through and through,

15:36.312 --> 15:38.712
but there's no denying
I'm pretty.

15:38.714 --> 15:41.515
Not as pretty as a young
Denzel, but you'll do.

15:41.517 --> 15:48.622
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:50.526 --> 15:52.493
Where's Harvey?

15:52.495 --> 15:54.261
Oh, you don't need to worry
about where Harvey is, Stanley.

15:54.263 --> 15:55.696
I'm handling this negotiation.
- Oh, I get it.

15:55.698 --> 15:57.531
He didn't have the balls
to face me,

15:57.533 --> 15:59.166
so he dumped it on you.
- He didn't dump anything.

15:59.168 --> 16:00.401
I wanted to be here.
- Well, Sparky,

16:00.403 --> 16:02.136
unless you also
wanna be in court,

16:02.138 --> 16:03.537
you better have those job
offers for my clients.

16:03.539 --> 16:05.506
Your clients want jobs?
Here they are.

16:07.743 --> 16:09.777
You're telling me Eli Gould
wants to hire them?

16:09.779 --> 16:12.546
Yes, he does, because your
clients are not damaged goods.

16:12.548 --> 16:16.350
They are hot commodities.
And these offers are the proof.

16:16.352 --> 16:18.352
- Spare me the bullshit.
- You don't like bullshit?

16:18.354 --> 16:20.754
Then why don't you admit the
second we hire those partners,

16:20.756 --> 16:22.289
they vote us out,

16:22.291 --> 16:23.691
sell the firm
to Rand Kaldor Zane,

16:23.693 --> 16:25.559
and you make a seven-figure
finder's fee?

16:25.561 --> 16:27.294
You're right.
That's the plan.

16:27.296 --> 16:28.796
I gotta admit, I didn't think
you'd figure it out.

16:28.798 --> 16:30.531
And you can take that plan
and shove it up your asshole,

16:30.533 --> 16:31.632
because there's not gonna be
any settlement.

16:31.634 --> 16:33.267
Then you've got a problem.

16:33.269 --> 16:35.703
Because you may have found
something on Eli.

16:35.705 --> 16:37.438
But turns out...

16:37.440 --> 16:39.707
I got more.

16:39.709 --> 16:42.576
- Bullshit, you're bluffing.
- Pick up the phone.

16:42.578 --> 16:44.545
Ask Eli if those offers
are still valid.

16:44.547 --> 16:46.714
They're not.
And not only that,

16:46.716 --> 16:49.550
we go to trial, he writes me
an affidavit saying

16:49.552 --> 16:51.385
you extorted him
to employ those partners

16:51.387 --> 16:53.287
after he told you
there's no way

16:53.289 --> 16:56.190
he'd ever hire a single lawyer
that came from your firm.

16:56.192 --> 16:57.591
- What do you want?
- You know what I want.

16:57.593 --> 16:59.460
But I'll tell you what.
Since Harvey's not here,

16:59.462 --> 17:01.262
you take my offer right now,

17:01.264 --> 17:03.497
I might even leave your name up
on the new firm.

17:03.499 --> 17:06.233
Get out of my sight,
you smug piece of shit.

17:06.234 --> 17:08.368
It's your funeral.

17:08.371 --> 17:09.603
See you in court, Sparky.

17:09.605 --> 17:12.606
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

17:12.608 --> 17:15.876
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:18.614 --> 17:21.382
Hey, what's going on?
I got your message.

17:21.384 --> 17:23.483
We just blew a small fortune
on jack shit.

17:23.486 --> 17:25.618
Don't tell me the soil
reports still didn't come in.

17:25.621 --> 17:28.454
Worse.
Those samples came back.

17:28.457 --> 17:30.524
And they're all negative.
- Negative?

17:30.526 --> 17:33.294
No, there's no way.
- It's right here, Mike.

17:33.296 --> 17:34.528
Then they must not have
tested deep enough to--

17:34.530 --> 17:36.363
They took samples
down to 10 feet.

17:36.365 --> 17:37.631
There isn't enough lead
in there to fill a pencil.

17:37.633 --> 17:39.233
Oh, my God.
I don't believe this.

17:39.235 --> 17:40.701
They fixed the results.
- They did,

17:40.703 --> 17:41.869
but not how you think.

17:41.871 --> 17:43.470
Six months ago,
the school got

17:43.472 --> 17:45.439
an anonymous donation
to redo its grounds.

17:45.441 --> 17:46.874
They called it
a beautification project.

17:46.876 --> 17:48.509
And let me guess.
They beautified

17:48.511 --> 17:50.244
every inch of soil
down to 10 feet.

17:50.246 --> 17:51.645
Yeah, and I didn't think
anything of it at the time

17:51.647 --> 17:53.247
because the plans just said
it was adding new trees.

17:53.249 --> 17:54.548
Oh, God.
Those fuckers.

17:54.550 --> 17:56.517
They knew this was coming.

17:56.519 --> 17:57.685
And then they got rid
of the evidence.

17:57.687 --> 17:59.520
- Mike.
- Rachel, please tell me

17:59.522 --> 18:02.256
you found something.
- I did, but it's not good.

18:02.258 --> 18:03.791
- What now?
- I did some checking.

18:03.793 --> 18:06.527
Mike, Andy Forsyth's been
in Seattle for the past year

18:06.529 --> 18:07.728
opening his own firm.

18:07.730 --> 18:09.396
The job was real.

18:09.398 --> 18:10.764
He had nothing to do

18:10.766 --> 18:13.267
with cutting the funding
for the clinic.

18:13.269 --> 18:15.536
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:15.538 --> 18:17.304
Okay, we might not have a way
to get them on that,

18:17.306 --> 18:18.806
but we know that they did this.

18:18.808 --> 18:20.474
We need to find the connection

18:20.476 --> 18:21.909
between
this beautification project

18:21.911 --> 18:24.545
and Discharge Power,
and we need to find it now.

18:24.547 --> 18:31.552
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:31.554 --> 18:34.321
I went to every single
meeting at the city council.

18:34.323 --> 18:36.290
They promised
to build new apartments

18:36.292 --> 18:37.625
before they tore
this place down.

18:37.627 --> 18:39.693
I've got the contract
right here, see?

18:39.695 --> 18:41.562
Memorandum of Agreement.

18:41.564 --> 18:43.364
And how did you feel
when you found out

18:43.366 --> 18:46.300
a Memorandum of Agreement
isn't legally enforceable?

18:46.302 --> 18:48.836
I felt like a fool.
That's what I felt like.

18:48.838 --> 18:50.638
That apartment is my home.

18:50.640 --> 18:52.673
I've paid rent on it
for 51 years.

18:52.675 --> 18:55.809
I live there with my daughter
and my grandchildren.

18:55.811 --> 18:58.579
This is our community,
our home.

18:58.581 --> 19:00.581
And we don't deserve
to be thrown out in the street

19:00.583 --> 19:02.916
like dogs.
- No, Lillian, you don't.

19:02.918 --> 19:05.819
But the developer's saying
there's other housing available

19:05.821 --> 19:07.621
out there for you.
- Maybe.

19:07.623 --> 19:09.390
But he didn't say none of that

19:09.392 --> 19:11.425
when he asked us
to sign on that dotted line.

19:11.427 --> 19:13.727
And a man who would lie like
that would...

19:13.729 --> 19:16.630
sell his own mother
to make a dollar.

19:16.632 --> 19:18.599
Thank you.

19:21.470 --> 19:23.537
I'm glad you brought up
the question of character,

19:23.539 --> 19:26.840
Ms. Cook, because I'd like
to ask you about yours.

19:26.842 --> 19:28.742
I don't have
anything to hide.

19:28.744 --> 19:32.746
Ms. Cook, are you related
to anyone in this courtroom?

19:32.748 --> 19:34.715
- What?
- It's a simple question.

19:34.717 --> 19:37.384
Are you a relative
of anyone in this room?

19:37.386 --> 19:39.620
And I'd like to point out
you lie under oath,

19:39.622 --> 19:43.357
the state penitentiary
will be your next home.

19:43.359 --> 19:44.892
Jessica Pearson is my niece.

19:44.894 --> 19:47.728
Well, isn't that
a small world?

19:47.730 --> 19:49.596
- Relevance?
- The relevance is that

19:49.598 --> 19:51.765
Jessica Pearson
is using her own aunt

19:51.767 --> 19:54.001
to make a name for herself.
- That's not true.

19:54.003 --> 19:56.970
My niece cares about the people
of my community.

19:56.972 --> 19:59.840
And after a lifetime
of no contact,

19:59.842 --> 20:03.577
did she call you to offer help,
or did you call her?

20:03.579 --> 20:04.912
She called me,
but--

20:04.914 --> 20:06.547
So you're telling the court

20:06.549 --> 20:08.649
she contacted you
out of nowhere

20:08.651 --> 20:11.652
because she cares
about the people of Chicago?

20:11.654 --> 20:13.587
Your Honor,
Ms. Cook can't speak to that.

20:13.589 --> 20:15.823
No, she can't.
But somehow she has.

20:15.825 --> 20:17.958
And, Your Honor, you said
if you found Jessica Pearson

20:17.960 --> 20:19.560
to be using a straw man,

20:19.562 --> 20:21.028
you would remove
her power of attorney.

20:21.030 --> 20:23.497
If this isn't proof of that,
then I don't know what is.

20:23.499 --> 20:24.665
- Your Honor--
- I agree.

20:24.667 --> 20:26.033
Ms. Pearson,
you're no longer permitted

20:26.035 --> 20:27.668
in my courtroom
on this matter.

20:27.670 --> 20:28.902
As for the TRO,

20:28.904 --> 20:31.739
you'll have my ruling
within 48 hours.

20:31.741 --> 20:33.407
[gavel pounds]

20:33.409 --> 20:35.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:35.044 --> 20:37.978
- What the hell?
- What the hell, what?

20:37.980 --> 20:40.581
When were you gonna tell me
who this woman was?

20:40.583 --> 20:42.049
I didn't keep it from you,
Harvey.

20:42.051 --> 20:43.851
Oh, bullshit.
I spent half the night

20:43.853 --> 20:46.019
with her last night,
and there is no way

20:46.021 --> 20:47.821
that doesn't come up
unless you hid it from me.

20:47.823 --> 20:49.523
What difference does it make

20:49.525 --> 20:50.924
that I have a personal
connection to this case?

20:50.926 --> 20:53.427
The difference is,
they just blindsided me.

20:53.429 --> 20:54.728
Harvey, I--

20:54.730 --> 20:58.599
Look, I put my firm
in jeopardy for you.

20:58.601 --> 21:01.635
You're playing me,
and I'm done with it.

21:01.637 --> 21:04.505
No, you can't be done.
I still need you.

21:04.507 --> 21:05.572
I don't give a shit
what you need.

21:05.574 --> 21:06.840
I'm getting on the next plane.

21:06.842 --> 21:09.510
You can finish
this thing yourself.

21:09.512 --> 21:10.911
What do you want me to say,
Harvey?

21:10.913 --> 21:13.981
That my father grew up here?
And he was poor?

21:13.983 --> 21:16.617
And I didn't live
on Park Avenue

21:16.619 --> 21:19.887
for the first ten years
of my life?

21:19.889 --> 21:22.055
'Cause I didn't.

21:23.759 --> 21:26.059
I didn't know that.

21:26.061 --> 21:28.529
Now you do.

21:29.799 --> 21:31.765
Well, what does all of that
have to do with this?

21:31.767 --> 21:34.034
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:34.036 --> 21:36.637
My father died
eight weeks ago.

21:36.639 --> 21:38.839
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:38.841 --> 21:42.042
That woman is his sister.

21:42.044 --> 21:45.913
And he turned his back on her
and everyone else here.

21:45.915 --> 21:50.517
And it ate away at him
for his entire life.

21:50.519 --> 21:52.820
So you decided
to do something about it.

21:52.822 --> 21:54.855
Yes, I did.

21:56.659 --> 21:58.725
Okay.

22:00.029 --> 22:03.831
- Okay, what?
- I know you have a plan.

22:03.833 --> 22:06.133
Tell me what you need.

22:10.005 --> 22:12.506
I'm trying to figure out
which costs more.

22:12.508 --> 22:14.041
The King of the Jungle
up there

22:14.043 --> 22:15.676
or putting the mayor in office.

22:15.678 --> 22:18.645
I put that thing down myself.

22:18.647 --> 22:21.114
You know, and I'm trying to
figure out why you New Yorkers

22:21.116 --> 22:23.050
don't know how
to make an appointment.

22:23.052 --> 22:26.687
What I know, Mr. McGann,
is how to make a deal.

22:26.689 --> 22:29.823
Yeah, well, after what
happened in court this morning,

22:29.825 --> 22:31.158
I don't think I need to.

22:31.160 --> 22:32.826
If you think you got this
in the bag,

22:32.828 --> 22:34.895
you are dead wrong.

22:34.897 --> 22:37.531
But you are right
about one thing.

22:37.533 --> 22:39.766
Jessica Pearson wants
to make a name for herself,

22:39.768 --> 22:41.802
starting with a seat
on city council.

22:41.804 --> 22:43.570
And what does that have
to do with me?

22:43.572 --> 22:45.706
Because all you have to do
to make this thing to away

22:45.708 --> 22:47.074
is give back enough units
to make it look like

22:47.076 --> 22:48.809
she got a win.

22:48.811 --> 22:51.078
Guarantee her aunt a spot
in the new building,

22:51.080 --> 22:53.814
then back her when she runs.
- Anything else?

22:53.816 --> 22:56.884
You want a park or a bridge
named after her?

22:56.886 --> 22:58.685
Yeah, there is
one more thing.

22:58.687 --> 22:59.953
You're not just
gonna endorse her.

22:59.955 --> 23:01.655
You're gonna make a donation.

23:01.657 --> 23:03.123
Because without it,
everybody's gonna know

23:03.125 --> 23:06.894
it's bullshit.
- You people.

23:06.896 --> 23:08.996
You think I'm gonna
give that woman a dime?

23:08.998 --> 23:10.864
That's the beauty of it, Pat.

23:10.866 --> 23:12.799
You don't have
to give her a penny.

23:16.739 --> 23:17.971
A million dollars.

23:17.973 --> 23:19.973
Cashier's check.
Untraceable.

23:19.975 --> 23:22.843
All you're doing
is giving her own money back.

23:22.845 --> 23:25.746
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

23:25.748 --> 23:29.016
Just so we're clear...

23:29.018 --> 23:31.618
Your client's dealing her way
into office.

23:31.620 --> 23:33.720
That's the Chicago way,
isn't it?

23:33.722 --> 23:35.122
So is when she gets there,

23:35.124 --> 23:37.124
she remembers
who did this for her.

23:37.126 --> 23:40.961
She wouldn't have it
any other way.

23:47.603 --> 23:50.471
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

23:50.473 --> 23:55.743
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:55.745 --> 23:58.145
- Well?
- It didn't work.

23:58.147 --> 23:59.981
What the hell do you mean,
it didn't work?

23:59.983 --> 24:01.582
I mean I went back to Gould,

24:01.584 --> 24:03.584
and he told me he doesn't care
what we have on those tapes.

24:03.586 --> 24:05.720
He's not helping us
because Gordon's got worse.

24:05.722 --> 24:07.621
Well, then what the hell
do you suggest?

24:07.623 --> 24:09.056
We can't go to court.

24:09.058 --> 24:11.025
The second we sign those
partners back,

24:11.027 --> 24:13.427
we're gonna be signing
our own death warrants.

24:13.429 --> 24:14.628
Not necessarily.

24:14.630 --> 24:16.163
What do you mean,
not necessarily?

24:16.165 --> 24:18.065
I mean if we make
the deal sweet enough,

24:18.067 --> 24:19.467
when they come back over,
they'll forget all about

24:19.469 --> 24:20.735
Rand and Kaldor's promises.

24:20.737 --> 24:22.536
And that would work

24:22.538 --> 24:25.573
except for the fact that
there are years of bad blood

24:25.575 --> 24:27.608
between me, Harvey,
and every one of those people.

24:27.610 --> 24:30.177
They don't trust us.
- But maybe they'll trust me.

24:30.179 --> 24:32.480
- What?
- I know this sounds crazy.

24:32.482 --> 24:33.714
But if you make me Managing
Partner until we can--

24:33.716 --> 24:35.616
I don't believe this.

24:35.618 --> 24:37.685
Harvey leaves for two days,
and you wanna throw his shit

24:37.687 --> 24:39.420
into the street?
- I'm not saying that.

24:39.422 --> 24:41.088
Well, it sure as hell sounds
like you are.

24:41.090 --> 24:42.656
God damn it, Louis,
I'm trying the best I can.

24:42.658 --> 24:44.392
Well, then try something else.

24:44.394 --> 24:45.726
Because giving you the reins

24:45.728 --> 24:47.628
a half hour
before we drive off a cliff

24:47.630 --> 24:49.397
isn't gonna do shit.

24:49.399 --> 24:55.202
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:59.142 --> 25:00.708
[lock clicks]

25:02.111 --> 25:05.646
Hey.
Uh, can I come in?

25:05.648 --> 25:08.215
It's late.
Everyone's sleeping.

25:08.217 --> 25:11.452
Please.
I'll only be a minute.

25:17.660 --> 25:19.693
I'm sorry about what happened
this morning.

25:19.695 --> 25:21.629
I know they used your mother

25:21.631 --> 25:23.164
to try to paint me
as self-serving, but--

25:23.166 --> 25:25.132
Look, that's all well
and good, Jessica.

25:25.134 --> 25:29.136
But right now, I'm wondering
if it's them using her or you.

25:29.138 --> 25:30.805
Angela, I'm not
using your mother.

25:30.807 --> 25:32.706
Then why did they give us
our choice of apartments

25:32.708 --> 25:34.542
if she sells out
everyone around us?

25:34.544 --> 25:37.144
- Who's they?
- That's all you have to say?

25:37.146 --> 25:38.813
Who's they?

25:38.815 --> 25:41.148
No, I didn't mean it
that way.

25:41.150 --> 25:44.418
Look, "they" is the lady
you say is using us.

25:44.420 --> 25:46.854
She told us all about the deal
your handsome friend is making.

25:46.856 --> 25:49.123
Angela, that woman
is not your friend.

25:49.125 --> 25:50.224
She's trying to--

25:50.226 --> 25:52.726
I know
what she's trying to do.

25:52.728 --> 25:55.162
I wanna know
what you're trying to do.

25:55.164 --> 25:57.665
I'm trying to reconnect
with my family.

25:59.168 --> 26:02.169
And make things better
at the same time.

26:03.706 --> 26:07.441
I remember when you first
started coming around here.

26:07.443 --> 26:10.744
My mother was so happy.
She just took you right in,

26:10.746 --> 26:12.847
'cause that's all
she ever wanted.

26:12.849 --> 26:14.849
And don't get me wrong,
I got nothing against you.

26:14.851 --> 26:18.219
But your famous surgeon father,
he turned his back on us.

26:18.221 --> 26:20.287
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

26:20.289 --> 26:22.289
And from what I can tell,
you're no different.

26:22.291 --> 26:24.792
No, the difference is
I'm trying to get to know you.

26:24.794 --> 26:26.827
Well, if you knew us,
you'd know that selling out

26:26.829 --> 26:29.196
the people around us
ain't gonna make things better.

26:29.198 --> 26:31.866
[door creaks]

26:33.269 --> 26:34.802
Come here, baby.

26:34.804 --> 26:41.909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:43.679 --> 26:45.846
[door opens and closes]

26:45.848 --> 26:51.252
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:55.224 --> 26:56.891
Wait a second.

26:57.927 --> 27:00.294
When did you say
the beautification happened?

27:00.296 --> 27:02.763
They redid the entire grounds
six weeks after we filed suit.

27:02.765 --> 27:03.864
That doesn't make
any sense.

27:03.866 --> 27:05.833
Six weeks is nothing.

27:05.835 --> 27:08.569
Something like this doesn't
happen without planning.

27:08.571 --> 27:10.838
Which means they didn't just
know they had liability

27:10.840 --> 27:12.640
after we brought the suit.

27:12.642 --> 27:14.275
They knew they had it
long before that.

27:14.277 --> 27:15.509
Of course they knew.
The question is,

27:15.511 --> 27:16.744
how do we prove it?

27:16.746 --> 27:18.312
No, I think
what Mike's saying is,

27:18.314 --> 27:19.847
they knew they had liability.

27:19.849 --> 27:21.815
So they must've had
liability insurance.

27:21.817 --> 27:23.617
- They always do.
- Yeah, but when they know

27:23.619 --> 27:25.352
they need it,
they get more.

27:25.354 --> 27:26.654
I mean, think about it.

27:26.656 --> 27:28.856
Collins offered us
100,000 a family

27:28.858 --> 27:31.692
inside of 15 seconds.
- Okay, hold on.

27:31.694 --> 27:32.826
I'm getting confused
about the math.

27:32.828 --> 27:34.562
Then how's this for math?

27:34.564 --> 27:36.664
The settlement he offered
is exactly five times

27:36.666 --> 27:38.299
what they're normally
insured for.

27:38.301 --> 27:40.935
And if a bus driver takes out
a policy for $10 million

27:40.937 --> 27:43.270
and his wife runs him over
with a bus,

27:43.272 --> 27:46.907
that's not a coincidence.
- Mike, I need to talk to you.

27:46.909 --> 27:48.642
- Donna, what is it?
- It's Louis.

27:48.644 --> 27:49.910
What about him?
I just talked to him earlier.

27:49.912 --> 27:51.612
He was fine.
- He's not fine.

27:51.614 --> 27:52.813
He needs your help,
and I'm here to make sure

27:52.815 --> 27:54.682
that he gets it.

27:54.684 --> 27:56.784
- Donna, this--
- Mike, Harvey said something

27:56.786 --> 27:59.720
like this might happen.
You gave him your word.

27:59.722 --> 28:02.823
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:02.825 --> 28:05.326
- Let's go.
- Mike.

28:05.328 --> 28:06.961
We got this.

28:06.963 --> 28:09.964
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:14.003 --> 28:15.402
How did you get in here?

28:15.404 --> 28:16.837
What the hell's
wrong with you?

28:16.839 --> 28:18.339
You had no goddamn business
calling my aunt.

28:18.341 --> 28:19.840
Sorry to disappoint you,

28:19.842 --> 28:21.842
but we're not entering
into an agreement

28:21.844 --> 28:23.978
without making sure all of
the parties are on board.

28:23.980 --> 28:25.746
And it's up to me
to deliver her.

28:25.748 --> 28:27.314
Did you really think
that we weren't gonna do

28:27.316 --> 28:29.316
our due diligence?
I know you think Harvard

28:29.318 --> 28:30.818
is the only law school
in the country,

28:30.820 --> 28:32.319
but we have a pretty good one
here too,

28:32.321 --> 28:34.021
and I was president
of its law review.

28:34.023 --> 28:36.590
I don't give a shit
if you're the Sultan of Brunei.

28:36.592 --> 28:37.691
You're gonna set up
that meeting

28:37.693 --> 28:39.593
between me and the mayor.

28:39.595 --> 28:40.861
And I don't know how many
times I have to tell you this.

28:40.863 --> 28:42.830
That's not gonna happen.

28:42.832 --> 28:44.632
And I know what you're
gonna ask him,

28:44.634 --> 28:46.267
and the answer's no.
He's never gonna cut me loose.

28:46.269 --> 28:47.701
Now, why would
I ask him that?

28:47.703 --> 28:49.036
Because we both
know you're right.

28:49.038 --> 28:50.904
I was the one who went
after your license.

28:50.906 --> 28:52.873
But if you think he's gonna get
rid of me for that...

28:52.875 --> 28:54.708
[laughs]

28:54.710 --> 28:55.909
You don't understand the way
thing work around here.

28:55.911 --> 28:57.911
Oh, I understand
how things work.

28:57.913 --> 29:01.482
And it's been going on
since the beginning of time.

29:04.320 --> 29:06.887
He keeps me around
because I do what it takes

29:06.889 --> 29:09.290
without having to be asked.

29:09.292 --> 29:10.758
I don't complain about it

29:10.760 --> 29:12.860
and it never comes back on him.

29:12.862 --> 29:14.962
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

29:14.964 --> 29:17.798
So you get your aunt on board
or don't.

29:17.800 --> 29:20.668
But don't ever come in here
thinking the mayor is gonna be

29:20.670 --> 29:22.403
the answer to your
problems again.

29:22.405 --> 29:24.905
I don't need the mayor, Keri.

29:24.907 --> 29:27.041
Because I have the man you said

29:27.043 --> 29:31.345
was the real player here
in the first place.

29:31.347 --> 29:32.880
So if I were you,

29:32.882 --> 29:35.449
I'd start brushing up
on my résumé.

29:35.451 --> 29:40.854
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:40.856 --> 29:42.456
- How'd it go?
<i>- Change of plans.</i>

29:42.458 --> 29:43.924
<i>You're calling Pat McGann</i>
<i>and telling him</i>

29:43.926 --> 29:45.793
<i>it's me or her.</i>

29:45.795 --> 29:47.895
Jessica, they don't know you.
You can't ask that much.

29:47.897 --> 29:49.663
<i>- Yes, I can.</i>
- I'm telling you,

29:49.665 --> 29:50.898
it's a bad idea.

29:50.900 --> 29:52.666
And I need you
to do it anyway.

29:52.668 --> 29:59.773
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:00.676 --> 30:04.712
- Need a lift?
- I have a car coming.

30:04.714 --> 30:06.680
Thanks.
- You sure?

30:06.682 --> 30:09.950
Beautiful woman downtown
all alone middle of the night.

30:09.952 --> 30:11.919
It isn't safe.

30:13.456 --> 30:15.522
And isn't your usual route
the airport?

30:15.524 --> 30:17.424
My work takes me
all kinds of places.

30:17.426 --> 30:19.026
And what exactly
is your work?

30:19.028 --> 30:22.396
I make problems go away.
And I love my job.

30:22.398 --> 30:24.698
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

30:24.700 --> 30:26.433
You think you can scare me
with your threats?

30:26.435 --> 30:27.935
Lady, if all I did
were make threats,

30:27.937 --> 30:30.137
then I wouldn't
even have a job.

30:30.139 --> 30:33.974
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:33.976 --> 30:36.744
Looks like your ride's here
after all.

30:36.746 --> 30:39.580
You have a safe night.

30:46.856 --> 30:48.789
- Where the hell were you?
- The police came.

30:48.791 --> 30:49.990
They told me I couldn't
stay here.

30:49.992 --> 30:51.024
I had to drive
around the block.

30:51.026 --> 30:54.461
Next time, goddamn text me.

30:54.463 --> 30:57.398
Ma'am, are you okay?

30:57.400 --> 30:59.800
Just take me home.

31:08.010 --> 31:11.044
Louis,
are you working in here?

31:11.046 --> 31:12.746
Sometimes I like
to sit at my old desk

31:12.748 --> 31:14.748
after everyone's gone.

31:14.750 --> 31:16.150
What are you doing here?

31:16.152 --> 31:18.152
I, uh, thought maybe you
could use some help

31:18.154 --> 31:20.888
on the Gordon lawsuit.
- What about the clinic?

31:20.890 --> 31:22.956
You said you were
in the middle of it.

31:22.958 --> 31:25.058
Ah, that's okay.

31:25.060 --> 31:27.528
Rachel and Oliver
are working on it.

31:27.530 --> 31:28.996
Donna told you,
didn't she?

31:28.998 --> 31:30.898
- Yeah, she did.
- God damn it.

31:30.900 --> 31:32.566
She was just
doing her job, Louis.

31:32.568 --> 31:35.936
It's not her job to get you
to bail me out, Mike.

31:37.773 --> 31:40.007
Louis...

31:41.610 --> 31:44.111
It's not your fault.
- That statement was my idea.

31:44.113 --> 31:46.213
I went to Gordon with it
in the first place.

31:46.215 --> 31:48.182
And we can pretend that

31:48.184 --> 31:50.584
it's not what got us here,
but it is.

31:50.586 --> 31:52.920
Well, right now, I'm less
concerned with what got us here

31:52.922 --> 31:55.489
than what's gonna get us out.
- You have an idea?

31:55.491 --> 31:57.224
I do.

31:57.226 --> 32:00.527
They want us to offer them
partnerships here.

32:00.529 --> 32:02.095
So what if we do that

32:02.097 --> 32:04.865
but we also ask Zane
to come over

32:04.867 --> 32:07.067
and to bring enough people
so that we can outvote them?

32:07.069 --> 32:08.202
Zane would never go for it.

32:08.204 --> 32:09.970
We've asked him
a thousand times.

32:09.972 --> 32:12.005
Have we ever asked him
right after Rand and Kaldor

32:12.007 --> 32:13.607
cut his legs out?

32:13.609 --> 32:15.542
[chuckles]

32:15.544 --> 32:16.977
What about Harvey?
He comes back to find out

32:16.979 --> 32:18.645
we've merged--
- He trusted us enough

32:18.647 --> 32:20.614
to take care of this.

32:20.616 --> 32:22.249
If this is what we have to do,

32:22.251 --> 32:25.586
then this is
what we have to do.

32:25.588 --> 32:29.189
You make sure they get
the offer in the morning.

32:29.191 --> 32:31.625
Leave the rest to me.

32:38.402 --> 32:40.936
First Louis, then Rachel.

32:40.938 --> 32:42.604
My money was
on Harvey being next.

32:42.606 --> 32:44.573
He's in Chicago
helping Jessica.

32:44.575 --> 32:46.374
He's in Chicago?

32:46.376 --> 32:48.910
When his firm is
in an all out war?

32:48.912 --> 32:51.513
We're a family, Robert.
We told him we'd have his back.

32:51.515 --> 32:53.481
Uh-huh.

32:53.483 --> 32:56.218
Then get to it.

32:56.220 --> 32:58.253
The world thinks my heart lies
with you, anyway.

32:58.255 --> 32:59.921
So you might as well
tell me what you need.

32:59.923 --> 33:01.356
Right, I don't know
how to say this,

33:01.358 --> 33:04.259
so I'm just gonna say it.

33:04.261 --> 33:05.860
We need you to come over
and join the firm.

33:05.862 --> 33:07.395
- What?
- You come over,

33:07.397 --> 33:09.264
you bring 20 people
who are loyal to you,

33:09.266 --> 33:10.632
and we will have enough votes
to still keep control.

33:10.634 --> 33:12.267
Okay, let me
get this straight.

33:12.269 --> 33:13.535
You want me to sneak out
of my own house

33:13.537 --> 33:15.437
in the middle of the night?

33:15.439 --> 33:17.339
You're talking about a place
I built with my own two hands.

33:17.341 --> 33:19.274
A place that we both know
isn't yours anymore.

33:19.276 --> 33:20.942
How is this even
supposed to work?

33:20.944 --> 33:22.644
Whose name comes first?
Who's the managing partner?

33:22.646 --> 33:24.379
We can work it out later.

33:24.381 --> 33:25.880
No, we're gonna work this out
goddamn now.

33:25.882 --> 33:28.883
- Well, I can't do that.
- Are you shitting me?

33:28.885 --> 33:30.452
Does Harvey
even know you're here?

33:30.454 --> 33:32.254
No, but he told us
to do whatever it takes

33:32.256 --> 33:33.888
to save the firm,
and as far as I can tell,

33:33.890 --> 33:36.258
this is the best way
to save both our asses.

33:36.260 --> 33:39.327
Would you leave your home?

33:39.329 --> 33:41.029
Would Jessica?

33:41.031 --> 33:43.465
Would Harvey?
Because I don't think so.

33:43.467 --> 33:45.267
Maybe not.
But like you said,

33:45.269 --> 33:47.369
the world thinks your heart
lies with us, anyway.

33:47.371 --> 33:49.271
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:49.273 --> 33:51.039
Maybe it really does.

33:51.041 --> 33:55.343
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:55.345 --> 33:56.645
Hey, how did it go
with Oliver?

33:56.647 --> 33:58.346
He got a lead
on the policies,

33:58.348 --> 33:59.514
but he can't get to them
till the morning.

33:59.516 --> 34:01.049
Good.

34:01.051 --> 34:03.952
- Well?
- Well, what?

34:03.954 --> 34:05.587
Did you talk to my dad?

34:05.589 --> 34:07.522
Louis told me.

34:09.025 --> 34:11.493
He said he'd think about it.

34:13.330 --> 34:17.065
So basically if my dad
doesn't come around by tomorrow,

34:17.067 --> 34:19.067
Specter Litt
could cease to exist.

34:19.069 --> 34:21.670
Which, ironically, means
the only way we still have jobs

34:21.672 --> 34:24.371
is if we're both working
for your dad.

34:27.543 --> 34:30.578
Unless we aren't.

34:30.580 --> 34:32.647
- What are you talking about?
- Mike, I went and saw

34:32.649 --> 34:35.483
Andy Forsyth today.

34:35.485 --> 34:37.018
That job still exists.

34:37.020 --> 34:38.920
Wait a second,
you went to see him

34:38.922 --> 34:41.322
about us moving to Seattle?
- I asked you what you would

34:41.324 --> 34:42.489
think if I said
I'd consider it.

34:42.492 --> 34:44.059
- Rachel--
- Just hear me out.

34:44.061 --> 34:46.561
And if you don't wanna do it,
we won't do it.

34:46.563 --> 34:49.364
But, Mike, we're young
and we don't have any kids yet.

34:49.366 --> 34:52.033
And if we're ever gonna
do something like this

34:52.034 --> 34:54.436
in our lives...

34:54.438 --> 34:56.705
now is the time.

34:58.642 --> 35:01.543
If we do this,
we'd have to leave within days.

35:01.545 --> 35:04.512
- I know.
- And what about the wedding?

35:04.514 --> 35:06.448
- What about it?
- We're not gonna fly back here

35:06.450 --> 35:10.952
in six weeks to have it.
- We could delay it.

35:10.954 --> 35:13.555
- I don't wanna delay it.
- We could move it up.

35:13.557 --> 35:15.724
Then let's move it up.

35:15.726 --> 35:17.659
I'm serious.
We can make that happen.

35:17.661 --> 35:21.029
Whoever can make it makes it.
Whoever can't can't.

35:21.031 --> 35:23.398
Wait, do you really wanna
take this job?

35:23.400 --> 35:25.066
I don't know if I wanna take
this job or not.

35:25.068 --> 35:27.602
But what I do know is that
I've wanted to marry you

35:27.604 --> 35:30.472
from the second I met you,
and I am tired of waiting.

35:30.474 --> 35:32.674
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:32.676 --> 35:34.709
So tomorrow Oliver's gonna find
the answer or not.

35:34.711 --> 35:37.712
Either way...

35:37.714 --> 35:39.614
we should do this.

35:39.616 --> 35:42.751
[laughs]
I can't believe it.

35:42.753 --> 35:46.388
It's so exciting.

35:46.390 --> 35:50.558
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:50.560 --> 35:51.760
[door opens]

35:51.762 --> 35:53.661
Oh, Jesus Christ.
What is it now?

35:53.663 --> 35:57.031
It's nothing bad,
but it is urgent.

35:57.033 --> 35:59.501
- What's going on?
- I don't wanna get into why,

35:59.503 --> 36:02.537
but Mike and I decided

36:02.539 --> 36:04.572
to move up the wedding.

36:04.574 --> 36:07.675
And we need a miracle worker
to make it happen.

36:07.677 --> 36:10.111
- Holy shit, are you sure?
- I'm not just sure.

36:10.113 --> 36:12.013
I'm excited.

36:12.015 --> 36:13.715
Then I just have
three questions for you.

36:13.717 --> 36:15.717
Band or DJ?
What kind of food?

36:15.719 --> 36:17.585
And rustic chic
or glam all the way?

36:17.587 --> 36:19.587
And if I thought you didn't
already have the answer

36:19.589 --> 36:20.789
to all those questions,
I wouldn't have come to you

36:20.791 --> 36:23.591
in the first place.

36:23.593 --> 36:26.628
- I love you, Rachel.
- I love you too, Donna.

36:26.630 --> 36:28.797
[both laugh softly]

36:30.000 --> 36:32.033
One more thing.

36:32.035 --> 36:33.034
You can't tell Harvey
or Jessica.

36:33.036 --> 36:35.036
- Rachel--
- Please.

36:35.038 --> 36:39.174
Mike and I don't want the start
of our new life to ruin theirs.

36:39.176 --> 36:40.542
Okay.

36:40.544 --> 36:42.744
[laughs]

36:42.746 --> 36:49.818
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:53.056 --> 36:55.089
- Ms. Pearson.
- Aren't you a gentleman.

36:55.091 --> 36:56.624
Well, I was taught
to stand for a lady.

36:56.626 --> 37:00.128
Whoever taught you
taught you well.

37:00.130 --> 37:02.197
I'm glad you decided to call.

37:02.199 --> 37:04.632
What's good here?

37:04.634 --> 37:07.669
I don't give a shit
what's good here.

37:07.671 --> 37:10.238
I just came to give you this.

37:13.510 --> 37:15.210
I'm not used to being stuck
with the check.

37:15.212 --> 37:16.611
And I'm not used
to being played

37:16.613 --> 37:18.513
by two assholes
from out of town.

37:18.515 --> 37:20.582
No one's playing anybody,
Pat.

37:20.584 --> 37:22.517
This is a simple
business transaction.

37:22.519 --> 37:23.785
Well, I don't do business
with people

37:23.787 --> 37:25.720
who force me
to fire my friends.

37:25.722 --> 37:27.655
Listen to me.
This doesn't have to--

37:27.657 --> 37:29.791
Enjoy your meal.
It's on me.

37:31.161 --> 37:33.194
Then I guess I'll see you
in court.

37:35.765 --> 37:38.066
Maybe.
But you're gonna have to have

37:38.068 --> 37:41.069
someone else handle
your case for you.

37:41.071 --> 37:44.272
- What did you do?
- I didn't do anything.

37:44.274 --> 37:46.274
See, apparently Mr. Slick
didn't follow all

37:46.276 --> 37:49.544
the procedures
for filing out of state.

37:49.546 --> 37:51.679
Turns out Judge Merrick's
a real stickler

37:51.681 --> 37:53.815
about these things.
But don't worry.

37:53.817 --> 37:55.650
I'm sure your boy's gonna
be able to reapply

37:55.652 --> 37:57.919
in another 12 months.

37:57.921 --> 38:04.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:06.530 --> 38:07.695
God damn it, Mike,
Gordon's about to get here,

38:07.697 --> 38:09.564
and I have to make a decision.

38:09.566 --> 38:11.733
I have not heard from you
and I have not heard from Zane.

38:11.735 --> 38:14.836
Please call me back
as soon as you get this.

38:14.838 --> 38:16.137
Okay, Louis.
I'm here.

38:16.139 --> 38:17.572
Court's starting
in ten minutes.

38:17.574 --> 38:18.840
So what is it?
We going to trial,

38:18.842 --> 38:20.842
or are you gonna take on
these partners?

38:24.314 --> 38:26.648
What the hell's going on?
Are we doing this or not?

38:26.650 --> 38:29.717
All right, Stanley, you win.

38:29.719 --> 38:31.819
Give me the agreement.

38:31.821 --> 38:33.621
Signed and ready to go.

38:38.795 --> 38:41.629
Stanley.

38:41.631 --> 38:43.164
Robert, what the hell
are you doing here?

38:43.166 --> 38:45.233
I just came to make sure
that the paperwork

38:45.235 --> 38:46.935
was in order
for your clients to come over

38:46.937 --> 38:50.138
and join our new firm.

38:50.140 --> 38:53.141
And before you can say
your little army can block it,

38:53.143 --> 38:55.310
it already happened this
morning while you were in here.

38:55.312 --> 38:57.779
You son of a bitch.
I always knew you had a thing

38:57.781 --> 38:59.647
for Jessica Pearson.
- You watch your mouth.

38:59.649 --> 39:02.150
Robert.
I got this.

39:02.152 --> 39:04.619
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

39:04.621 --> 39:08.222
Stanley, why don't you move
your fat face away from mine?

39:08.224 --> 39:11.326
Because I need to talk
to my new partner.

39:11.328 --> 39:14.228
Sparky.
- This isn't over.

39:14.230 --> 39:21.336
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:24.908 --> 39:26.874
Why the hell did you not
tell me about all of this?

39:26.876 --> 39:29.911
Because if there's one thing
I know about my new partner,

39:29.913 --> 39:31.779
if he would have known
what we were up to,

39:31.781 --> 39:33.815
he would have found a way
to shit it up.

39:33.817 --> 39:36.784
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:36.786 --> 39:39.253
One other thing.

39:39.255 --> 39:43.191
When Harvey gets back,
you tell him...

39:43.193 --> 39:45.360
my name goes up there first.

39:47.664 --> 39:49.764
What's going on?
Did the judge make a ruling?

39:49.766 --> 39:50.898
More like a statement.

39:50.900 --> 39:52.200
McGann had you
kicked off the case.

39:52.202 --> 39:53.668
What?
Bullshit.

39:53.670 --> 39:55.036
He can't get away with that.
- He can.

39:55.038 --> 39:57.672
But it doesn't matter anymore.

39:57.674 --> 39:59.641
I got this.
- Jessica, these people aren't

39:59.643 --> 40:01.209
messing around.
They do this to me,

40:01.211 --> 40:02.944
you don't know what else
they'll do.

40:02.946 --> 40:05.947
And my record is as good
on the road as it is at home.

40:05.949 --> 40:07.382
I'm sticking to the plan.

40:07.384 --> 40:08.916
Then I'm riding
shotgun with you.

40:08.918 --> 40:10.318
The hell you are.
You're going home.

40:10.320 --> 40:12.020
I'm not going anywhere.

40:12.022 --> 40:13.988
Harvey, when were you gonna
tell me Mike and Rachel

40:13.990 --> 40:15.723
moved up their wedding?
- When you were out of trouble,

40:15.725 --> 40:17.025
that's when.

40:17.027 --> 40:18.259
I didn't know myself
until an hour ago.

40:18.261 --> 40:19.894
Well, now you know.

40:19.896 --> 40:22.697
You're the closest thing
that kid has to family.

40:22.699 --> 40:24.365
If you're not there for him,
you're gonna regret it

40:24.367 --> 40:26.234
for the rest of your life.
- Jessica.

40:26.236 --> 40:29.804
Harvey.
This is my family here.

40:29.806 --> 40:31.939
I denied they existed
for too long,

40:31.941 --> 40:34.942
and I'm going
to take care of them.

40:34.944 --> 40:37.011
Now you need to go.

40:37.013 --> 40:40.882
Take care of yours.

40:40.884 --> 40:43.451
Be careful with these people.

40:45.055 --> 40:47.055
I will.

40:47.057 --> 40:54.328
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:55.999 --> 40:57.699
Before I ask you my question,

40:57.701 --> 40:58.833
I wanna make sure
you understand

40:58.835 --> 41:00.435
what the penalty
for perjury is.

41:00.437 --> 41:03.004
- I know what perjury is.
- And you also know that

41:03.006 --> 41:05.006
20 of your executives
pulled their kids

41:05.008 --> 41:07.408
from Treetop Elementary School
within the first six months

41:07.410 --> 41:08.876
of the plant opening.
- Objection.

41:08.878 --> 41:09.977
Relevance?
- The relevance is that

41:09.979 --> 41:11.479
they knew what they were doing.

41:11.481 --> 41:12.814
That's why they pulled
their kids from school,

41:12.816 --> 41:14.048
pulled soil from the ground.

41:14.050 --> 41:15.883
You have no proof of that.

41:15.885 --> 41:17.719
No, but I do have proof
that your client increased

41:17.721 --> 41:20.755
the insurance policy
on that plant to $15 million--

41:20.757 --> 41:22.890
the exact amount of
the settlement you offered us,

41:22.892 --> 41:25.426
and five times the amount
you have on any other plant.

41:25.428 --> 41:26.994
That was
a very generous offer.

41:26.996 --> 41:28.496
No, it's what you've been
prepared to pay

41:28.498 --> 41:30.064
for almost a year.
- That's not true.

41:30.066 --> 41:31.933
Which part isn't true?

41:31.935 --> 41:33.901
The insurance policy?
Because I have that right here.

41:33.903 --> 41:35.403
- Objection, badgering.
- Overruled.

41:35.405 --> 41:37.905
Mr. Evans,
I am asking you under oath,

41:37.907 --> 41:41.843
why is one plant insured for so
much more than all the others?

41:41.845 --> 41:44.479
I'm not in charge
of our insurance policies.

41:44.481 --> 41:46.347
Your name's on the policy.
Isn't that right?

41:46.349 --> 41:47.815
I remind you, Mr. Evans,
you're under oath.

41:47.817 --> 41:49.450
I'd like a moment
with my client.

41:49.452 --> 41:50.918
And I'd like him to answer
the goddamn question.

41:50.920 --> 41:52.754
The witness will answer
the question.

41:52.756 --> 41:54.922
- Why so much insurance?
- What do you want me to say?

41:54.924 --> 41:57.058
I want you to admit that
you knew the plant was toxic

41:57.060 --> 41:59.827
and you covered it up.
- All right, we knew.

41:59.829 --> 42:01.529
We took precautions,
but they didn't work.

42:01.531 --> 42:03.498
And the plant was
already open.

42:03.500 --> 42:05.533
So we offered
to make things right.

42:05.535 --> 42:08.035
What else do you want?

42:08.037 --> 42:10.471
What I want is for those kids
to have never gotten sick

42:10.473 --> 42:12.106
in the first place.

42:12.108 --> 42:13.407
But that's not
gonna happen now,

42:13.409 --> 42:16.377
thanks to you.

42:16.379 --> 42:18.846
You can't make this right.

42:18.848 --> 42:20.815
But you sure as hell
can do better

42:20.817 --> 42:22.884
than say each of these
innocent children's lives

42:22.886 --> 42:25.820
is only worth $100,000.

42:25.822 --> 42:31.392
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:31.394 --> 42:34.796
What's it gonna take?

42:34.798 --> 42:36.497
A million dollars a family.

42:36.499 --> 42:40.401
Right now.
Take it or leave it.

42:40.403 --> 42:42.503
Done.

42:42.505 --> 42:47.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:47.010 --> 42:48.509
I know you prefer
appointments,

42:48.511 --> 42:50.111
but you left something
at the restaurant.

42:50.113 --> 42:52.980
I didn't leave anything.

42:52.982 --> 42:54.949
- You left your leverage.
- What is this?

42:54.951 --> 42:57.985
It's a photo shoot starring
you giving me a cashier's check

42:57.987 --> 42:59.887
for $1 million.

42:59.889 --> 43:02.557
Not ten minutes before removing
my lawyer from the case

43:02.559 --> 43:06.527
and one day before I withdraw
my suit to shut you down.

43:06.529 --> 43:08.863
Which would mean I paid
you off to drop this thing.

43:08.865 --> 43:10.565
It sure does look that way,
doesn't it?

43:10.567 --> 43:12.967
You're willing to make it
look like you're that corrupt?

43:12.969 --> 43:16.003
Your people did that
when they took away my license.

43:16.005 --> 43:17.872
And now that I'm not
an attorney anymore,

43:17.874 --> 43:20.141
it's not illegal
for me to drop this thing.

43:20.143 --> 43:22.143
But for you to pay me
to drop it,

43:22.145 --> 43:23.878
that's a crime.
- I didn't pay you.

43:23.880 --> 43:25.847
Good luck convincing
a jury of that.

43:25.849 --> 43:30.952
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:30.954 --> 43:32.587
I will.

43:32.589 --> 43:34.622
Because that was
a cashier's check.

43:34.624 --> 43:36.424
It didn't come from me.

43:36.426 --> 43:38.059
And all you'd have to do
to prove that

43:38.061 --> 43:40.928
is to open up
your bank account.

43:40.930 --> 43:42.563
I didn't think so.

43:42.565 --> 43:45.099
And, Pat, this is
a federal housing project,

43:45.101 --> 43:47.869
so in case you're thinking
of trying anything funny,

43:47.871 --> 43:50.004
the judge, the jury,
and the prosecution

43:50.006 --> 43:53.875
will not be from Chicago.

43:53.877 --> 43:56.210
Have a good night.

44:01.018 --> 44:03.886
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

44:03.888 --> 44:09.258
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:09.260 --> 44:11.159
How's your night going?

44:11.161 --> 44:12.928
My night is just fine.

44:12.930 --> 44:14.396
And you can tell your boss
if he's still trying

44:14.398 --> 44:17.266
to intimidate me,
he's wasting his time.

44:17.268 --> 44:19.468
- Or you can tell him yourself.
- I just did.

44:19.470 --> 44:21.303
I'm not talking
about Patrick McGann.

44:21.305 --> 44:24.172
I'm talking about Mayor Novak.

44:24.174 --> 44:27.109
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:27.111 --> 44:29.478
- You work for the mayor?
- Yeah, I do.

44:29.480 --> 44:32.114
And he would like to see you
right now.

44:32.116 --> 44:34.016
And how do I know you're not
gonna take me somewhere

44:34.018 --> 44:36.251
and drop me off the roof
of a building?

44:36.253 --> 44:39.121
'Cause that's a city car,
I'm on duty,

44:39.123 --> 44:41.356
and we both know the man who
took your little photo shoot

44:41.358 --> 44:44.192
with Mr. McGann is camped out
across the street.

44:44.194 --> 44:46.995
- Then let's go.
- One condition.

44:46.997 --> 44:49.097
The paparazzi stays here.

44:49.099 --> 44:56.204
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:27.471 --> 45:29.972
This is pretty far
out of the way.

45:29.974 --> 45:32.274
I'm not even sure
we're in Chicago anymore.

45:32.276 --> 45:34.176
I usually try
to meet blackmailers

45:34.178 --> 45:36.178
outside the office.
- Just for the record,

45:36.180 --> 45:38.113
I'm not the one
who started this throwdown.

45:38.115 --> 45:40.015
It doesn't matter
who started it.

45:40.017 --> 45:41.483
We're here to finish it.
- What'd you have in mind?

45:41.485 --> 45:43.418
Guns or knives?
- I was thinking more along

45:43.420 --> 45:45.187
the lines of an embrace.

45:45.189 --> 45:46.755
Here's the thing, Ms. Pearson.

45:46.757 --> 45:48.490
Your little stunt

45:48.492 --> 45:50.359
could cost me the election,
no doubt about it.

45:50.361 --> 45:52.361
But if you pull the pin
on that grenade,

45:52.363 --> 45:54.129
I guarantee
the least that happens

45:54.131 --> 45:55.430
is your hand gets
blown off too.

45:55.432 --> 45:57.199
I'm waiting for
the embrace part.

45:57.201 --> 45:59.301
Well, here it is.
You're a formidable woman.

45:59.303 --> 46:02.104
Instead of creating problems
for me,

46:02.106 --> 46:03.238
you should be fixing them.

46:03.240 --> 46:05.007
Are you offering me a job?

46:05.009 --> 46:08.143
I'm offering you
an opportunity.

46:08.145 --> 46:10.145
What the hell does Pat McGann
have on you?

46:10.147 --> 46:11.380
We're not talking
about Pat.

46:11.382 --> 46:14.149
We're talking about you.
- Okay.

46:14.151 --> 46:16.051
Let's talk about me.

46:16.053 --> 46:18.153
Why the hell should I get
into bed with a man like you?

46:18.155 --> 46:20.622
Because you ran one of the
best law firms in New York.

46:20.624 --> 46:22.491
You had money, you had power,
you had influence.

46:22.493 --> 46:24.459
And you're gonna have to do
a hell of a lot better

46:24.461 --> 46:26.395
than that
because I left it all behind

46:26.397 --> 46:28.263
to make a difference.
- And how's that going?

46:28.265 --> 46:30.132
You're not even
a lawyer anymore.

46:30.134 --> 46:31.533
You really wanna
make a difference?

46:31.535 --> 46:34.369
Take this job.
Do things from the inside.

46:34.371 --> 46:36.605
It sounds like you want me
to clean up your messes.

46:36.607 --> 46:39.274
Not make a difference.
- I'm not a charity.

46:39.276 --> 46:41.443
I'm a politician.

46:41.445 --> 46:43.311
And you can't have one
without the other.

46:43.313 --> 46:45.547
Well, tell me this,
Mr. Mayor.

46:45.549 --> 46:47.516
How's your current number two
going to feel

46:47.518 --> 46:50.085
if I replace her?
Because if I come work for you,

46:50.087 --> 46:51.553
it's not gonna be
as number three.

46:51.555 --> 46:53.455
That's between you and her.

46:53.457 --> 46:55.824
The only thing
I give a shit about

46:55.826 --> 46:57.526
is that you drop that lawsuit

46:57.528 --> 47:00.429
and never mention the North Park
Housing Project again.

47:00.431 --> 47:02.164
- What?
- Did you really think

47:02.166 --> 47:03.398
you were gonna get something
for nothing here?

47:03.400 --> 47:05.300
The lawsuit disappears.

47:05.302 --> 47:07.202
That is nonnegotiable.

47:07.204 --> 47:09.438
- No way.
- What choice do you have?

47:09.440 --> 47:11.840
Your sidekick's gone.
You're off the case.

47:11.842 --> 47:13.341
- Bullshit.
- It's over anyway.

47:13.343 --> 47:14.843
Nothing is over.
I'll find a way.

47:14.845 --> 47:16.278
What the hell are you
fighting for?

47:16.280 --> 47:18.180
I made a promise
to my family.

47:18.182 --> 47:19.448
We'll take care
of your family.

47:19.450 --> 47:21.149
They don't want
taken care of.

47:21.151 --> 47:22.551
They want their community
taken care of.

47:22.553 --> 47:24.519
So figure out
how to do it working for me.

47:24.521 --> 47:27.556
'Cause I don't care what you
think you have on Pat McGann.

47:27.558 --> 47:30.392
That project's going up.

47:30.394 --> 47:33.195
And I need an answer
by tomorrow.

47:33.197 --> 47:40.268
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:44.208 --> 47:47.175
I can't believe
you actually pulled this off.

47:47.177 --> 47:50.312
Mm, yeah, you can.

47:50.314 --> 47:52.681
- You told him.
- Yeah, Mike, I did.

47:52.683 --> 47:55.383
'Cause Rachel trusted me
to put this wedding together,

47:55.385 --> 47:58.353
and it...wouldn't have felt
like a celebration

47:58.355 --> 48:00.355
without Harvey.

48:00.357 --> 48:02.224
Thanks, Donna.

48:02.226 --> 48:04.326
- See you up there.
- Yeah.

48:06.630 --> 48:09.231
[sighs]
Just in time.

48:09.233 --> 48:11.366
I didn't think you were gonna
be able to make it.

48:11.368 --> 48:14.703
What can I say?
I like to make an entrance.

48:14.705 --> 48:17.305
It's gonna be awkward
when my real best man shows up.

48:17.307 --> 48:20.375
Oh, I think it's clear
who the best man is.

48:20.377 --> 48:22.644
Mm, okay, maybe.

48:22.646 --> 48:24.613
Good.

48:24.615 --> 48:26.615
Not the best.

48:26.617 --> 48:29.618
Hey, you ready for this?

48:29.620 --> 48:32.187
Yeah, I am.

48:32.589 --> 48:34.456
I think you are too.

48:34.458 --> 48:37.225
<i>[tender piano music]</i>

48:37.227 --> 48:43.598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:43.600 --> 48:46.535
<i>From the first</i>
<i>second I met you,</i>

48:46.537 --> 48:48.537
<i>I knew I wanted to be here</i>
<i>with you someday.</i>

48:48.539 --> 48:51.673
<i>Walking down the aisle</i>
<i>arm in arm.</i>

48:51.675 --> 48:58.680
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:58.682 --> 49:00.715
<i>I know that</i>
<i>I fought it at first,</i>

49:00.717 --> 49:05.320
<i>but now, Mike, I can't imagine</i>
<i>living alongside anyone else</i>

49:05.322 --> 49:07.189
<i>for the rest of my life.</i>

49:07.191 --> 49:14.296
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:16.200 --> 49:18.266
<i>If I've learned one thing,</i>

49:18.268 --> 49:21.303
<i>it's that we never know</i>
<i>what the future holds.</i>

49:21.305 --> 49:23.505
<i>And that could be</i>
<i>a scary thing.</i>

49:23.507 --> 49:26.474
<i>But I know that there</i>
<i>is nothing that I can't handle</i>

49:26.476 --> 49:29.444
<i>when I have you by my side.</i>

49:29.446 --> 49:32.614
<i>You are the strongest man</i>
<i>I've ever met.</i>

49:32.616 --> 49:35.350
<i>And you make me stronger.</i>

49:35.352 --> 49:38.220
You're the husband
I've always wanted.

49:38.222 --> 49:40.522
And I can't wait to begin
our adventure together.

49:40.524 --> 49:42.791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:42.793 --> 49:45.694
Do you, Michael James Ross,

49:45.696 --> 49:47.996
take Rachel Elizabeth Zane

49:47.998 --> 49:51.466
to be your lawfully
wedded wife?

49:51.468 --> 49:53.235
I do.

49:53.237 --> 49:54.536
And do you, Rachel,
take Michael

49:54.538 --> 49:56.271
to be your
lawfully wedded husband?

49:56.273 --> 49:57.505
I do.

49:57.507 --> 50:00.475
Then I now pronounce you
man and wife.

50:00.477 --> 50:07.582
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:14.758 --> 50:18.593
[applause]

50:18.595 --> 50:25.700
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:42.519 --> 50:44.352
Cheers.

50:44.354 --> 50:46.655
I gotta say, Mike,
those were some beautiful vows.

50:46.657 --> 50:48.423
Especially the part
about family.

50:48.425 --> 50:49.624
Thanks, Harvey.

50:49.626 --> 50:51.393
And I didn't get
to say it before,

50:51.395 --> 50:54.062
but I'm really glad
you made it.

50:54.064 --> 50:56.698
Me too.
But I should be the one

50:56.700 --> 50:59.701
who's saying thank you.
You saved the firm.

50:59.703 --> 51:01.703
- Harvey--
- And before you say anything,

51:01.705 --> 51:03.805
let me just say I was wrong.

51:03.807 --> 51:06.741
You're senior partner material.
You are ready.

51:06.743 --> 51:08.743
And when you come back
from your honeymoon--

51:08.745 --> 51:10.912
We're not coming back,
Harvey.

51:10.914 --> 51:12.814
Rachel and I
were offered a chance

51:12.816 --> 51:14.482
to run a firm in Seattle.

51:14.484 --> 51:16.551
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

51:16.553 --> 51:19.454
It's a--it's a place that
only takes class action cases

51:19.456 --> 51:21.556
against "Fortune" 500 companies,
and...

51:21.558 --> 51:24.526
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:24.528 --> 51:27.362
Well, we decided to go for it.
- Mike--

51:27.364 --> 51:28.930
Harvey,
when Donna came to me,

51:28.932 --> 51:30.598
told me the firm
was in trouble,

51:30.600 --> 51:32.434
I did exactly
what I told you I would,

51:32.436 --> 51:33.601
but I don't ever wanna have

51:33.603 --> 51:34.936
to make a choice
like that again.

51:34.938 --> 51:36.438
You don't have to.

51:36.440 --> 51:37.906
If you wanna do more
pro Bono cases--

51:37.908 --> 51:40.709
That's not the point, Harvey,
and you know it.

51:40.711 --> 51:42.877
This is who I am.

51:42.879 --> 51:45.380
It's who I've always been.

51:45.382 --> 51:48.116
It's time, Harvey.

51:48.118 --> 51:49.918
It's time.

51:49.920 --> 51:57.392
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:13.877 --> 52:17.145
Jessica, good.
I'm glad you're here.

52:17.147 --> 52:19.514
I need to talk to you.
- I need to talk to you first.

52:19.516 --> 52:21.850
- What is it?
- Starting on Monday,

52:21.852 --> 52:23.818
I'm working for the mayor.
- What?

52:23.820 --> 52:25.987
- Jeff--
- You sold out your family?

52:25.989 --> 52:28.757
I didn't sell them out.
He's giving me an opportunity

52:28.759 --> 52:31.426
to change things
from the inside,

52:31.428 --> 52:32.560
and I'm taking it.

52:32.562 --> 52:33.895
Jessica, you're making
a mistake.

52:33.897 --> 52:36.398
I told you.
I can take care of myself.

52:36.400 --> 52:37.632
And what if you can't?

52:37.634 --> 52:38.833
What is that
supposed to mean?

52:38.835 --> 52:41.736
I talked to my friend
over at Justice.

52:41.738 --> 52:43.438
They're looking
at your new friends

52:43.440 --> 52:46.007
for the murder
of that original plaintiff.

52:46.009 --> 52:49.411
Which means if you get
into bed with them,

52:49.413 --> 52:51.613
you either end up
like that plaintiff,

52:51.615 --> 52:54.015
or you end up like them.

52:54.017 --> 52:56.785
What makes you think
I can't handle

52:56.787 --> 53:01.456
a local politician and
a shady real estate developer?

53:01.458 --> 53:04.993
So you've already
made up your mind?

53:04.995 --> 53:06.928
Yes.

53:06.930 --> 53:08.930
I have.

53:08.932 --> 53:11.533
Well...

53:11.535 --> 53:14.869
I just hope that you're
the first person in the world

53:14.871 --> 53:19.007
who can lie down with dogs
and not come up with fleas.

53:25.816 --> 53:28.817
<i>[somber music]</i>

53:28.819 --> 53:35.890
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:00.617 --> 54:02.650
Hey.

54:02.652 --> 54:06.488
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:06.490 --> 54:10.091
What do you say?

54:10.093 --> 54:12.760
I don't mind if I do.

